  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Gradient Descent
Category:    Optimization
Definition:  Iteratively adjusts parameters to minimize loss function
Year:        1847
Researchers: Cauchy; ML by many
Applications:Training all ML models
Related:     SGD, Adam, momentum, learning rate

Concept:     Transformer
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Attention-based model processing sequences in parallel
Year:        2017
Researchers: Vaswani et al.
Applications:LLMs, vision models, protein folding
Related:     GPT, BERT, attention mechanism

Concept:     CNN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Convolutional filters detect spatial features hierarchically
Year:        1989
Researchers: LeCun et al.
Applications:Image classification, object detection
Related:     Pooling, feature maps, ResNet

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Market Failure
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Free markets fail to allocate resources efficiently
Formula:    Social cost = private + external cost
Economist:  Arthur Pigou
Example:    Carbon emissions: negative externality requiring government intervention

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

